texts.text: >The Liberators failed to defeat Rahab in the other world.
>You returned home but struggle against the demon invasion.
It's over there, Rika!
Right! Ganesha, if you would!
*Trumpet*
Gah!
Order up!
You two make a great team.
Well, duh! Ooh, maybe it's the power of love?
I doubt love is involved, but we do have great teamwork.
Still...
Hmm? What's up?
This demon was nothing to me, yet I was nothing against Rahab.
I cannot deny my own weakness.
Rika...
C'mon, chin up. You'll spoil that adorable face.
Oh, I know! Let's all go to the other world next time!
We'll get revenge on Rahab with the power of love!
*Sigh* You're a real birdbrain, aren't you?
Where'd that come from? I'm just tryin' to cheer Rika up.
And who's a "birdbrain"? You sayin' my hair looks like a nest?
No, I'm saying your recall is shit.
Did you already forget only two people can go at a time?
Oh...
Yes, that's right.
Besides, last time wasn't even a close battle but total defeat.
Whoever goes will likely face the same dilemma.
Yep, that's our sad situation.
I wanna figure out a breakthrough strategy, but...
*Growl*
YUMMY HUMANS! SO TASTY!
Looks like that'll have to wait.
Yeah, our guests are impatient.
Man, I'm beat.
Our foe isn't limitless, but we still need reduce their numbers.
We must deal with them quickly.
A way to win in the other world...
One that can be accomplished by two people...
That'd be great, but...
Hmm...
We'll figure it out.
It sounds like you're just as troubled as me, Newbie.
If only an idea would come to mind...
Wishful thinking won't help anyone.
What we need is a solid plan, so get on it.
Please calm down. I can't think under pressure.
>Gears turn as the Liberators consider how to defeat Rahab.
Um—
I just thought of something. May I?
No.
Hey, at least hear me out!
We've got no plan and no time.
Whatever is in your head, I doubt it will fix anything.
Excuse me, even I can—

...!
Get down!
>Everyone flinches at Gakuto's warning. A second later—
>A huge, whip-like tentacle passes overhead.
Jeez! That was a close one!
That whip... Was it this guy?
Don't think you can escape me.
I wanted to chop off yer heads and watch the blood fly! *Snicker*
I'll admit we didn't see it comin'.
Watch out, y'all. He looks tougher than the rest.
We're already half-dead. But what do you care, right?
*Snicker* That ain't my problem.
You serve the Divine, which makes you the bad guys, glub.
Huh? I'm no one's lackey.
Apparently we've been lumped together.
What're the Divine up to anyway?
We've only seen those two messengers.
...Now that you mention it, yeah.
There hasn't been one showdown between angels and demons.
The other units haven't sent word either. Which means...
They're just up there watching us fight.
Those angels have it made.
*Snicker* Exactly. They're a cruel lot!
The cowards even tricked us and Lord Rahab, glub!
"Tricked"?
Time's up! Die, you Divine puppets!
>The Liberators fight despite their severe injuries.
>They continue switching between offense and defense, until...

*Snicker*
I lost. Too bad, glub...
No hard feelings, pal. We've got a lot at stake too.
Before ya disappear, lemme ask this:
What's Rahab's endgame?
I wasn't gonna talk, but fine.
You all fight hard. Not like those lazy angels.
Much appreciated.
We came here to get revenge on the Divine.
Revenge?
We lost to them a long time ago, glub.
But it wasn't in battle. They tricked us.
Those angels played dirty and stole our power beforehand.
That's how I became this weak, squishy jellyfish.
We had no choice but to flee to an alternate world, glub.
An alternate world... You mean the one Rahab destroyed?
You've been there, glub?
It was a mess when we arrived.
We found no sign of life, human or otherwise, glub.
It was a rough existence, but we got through it.
The Divine will know our wrath! Nothing else matters!
So, you waited to come here until the time was ripe.
Yes! Now that we've beefed up, they're the ones goin' down!
But now there's just one problem.
Oh yeah? What's that?
You humans, glub.
Seems while we were gone, the angels found their own weapon, glub.
Humans are real useful that way.
The Divine are restin' up and leavin' the dirty work to you.
What handy, powerful tools, glub. The powerful get more power.
Screw that! We ain't their weapon!
*Snicker* Can you really say that? You just beat me.
Lord Rahab... Please take revenge for me...
On both angels...and humans...
>The demon gives an eerie smile and disappears.
So, demons view us and the Divine the same way...
It ain't like we asked for any of this.
Regardless, they're still hostile.
It's beyond all logic.
